%% TrustyAI Explainability - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant MM as ModelMesh Serving
    participant KSL as KServe InferenceLogger
    participant TrustyAI as TrustyAI Service<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant MMR as ModelMesh Reconciler
    participant KSR as KServe Reconciler
    participant Storage as Storage Backend<br/>(PVC/MinIO/DB)
    participant Scheduler as PrometheusScheduler
    participant Prom as Prometheus Server
    participant Client as API Client
    participant KSModel as KServe Model Server<br/>gRPC v2

    Note over MM,Storage: Flow 1: ModelMesh Inference Payload Ingestion
    MM->>TrustyAI: POST /consumer/kserve/v2<br/>8080/TCP HTTP plaintext
    TrustyAI->>MMR: Forward payload (in-process)
    MMR->>MMR: Reconcile partial input/output<br/>into complete prediction
    MMR->>Storage: Store reconciled prediction

    Note over KSL,Storage: Flow 2: KServe CloudEvent Inference Ingestion
    KSL->>TrustyAI: CloudEvent (org.kubeflow.serving.inference.request)<br/>8080/TCP HTTP plaintext
    KSL->>TrustyAI: CloudEvent (org.kubeflow.serving.inference.response)<br/>8080/TCP HTTP plaintext
    TrustyAI->>KSR: Forward events (in-process)
    KSR->>KSR: Reconcile request/response<br/>into complete prediction
    KSR->>Storage: Store reconciled prediction

    Note over Scheduler,Prom: Flow 3: Scheduled Metric Computation & Export
    Scheduler->>Storage: Read inference data (scheduled)
    Storage-->>Scheduler: Prediction records
    Scheduler->>Scheduler: Compute fairness metrics (SPD, DIR)<br/>Compute drift metrics (KS, Meanshift, MMD)
    Scheduler->>Scheduler: Publish to Micrometer registry
    Prom->>TrustyAI: GET /q/metrics<br/>8080/TCP HTTP plaintext
    TrustyAI-->>Prom: Prometheus metrics (text/plain)

    Note over Client,KSModel: Flow 4: Explainability Request (Disabled in RHOAI)
    Client->>TrustyAI: POST /explainers/local/lime<br/>8080/TCP HTTP plaintext
    TrustyAI->>KSModel: Inference request<br/>gRPC KServe v2 plaintext
    KSModel-->>TrustyAI: Model predictions
    TrustyAI->>TrustyAI: Compute LIME explanation
    TrustyAI-->>Client: Explanation response (JSON)

    Note over Client,TrustyAI: Flow 5: On-demand Metric Request
    Client->>TrustyAI: POST /metrics/group/fairness/spd<br/>8080/TCP HTTP plaintext
    TrustyAI->>Storage: Read inference data
    Storage-->>TrustyAI: Prediction records
    TrustyAI->>TrustyAI: Compute SPD metric
    TrustyAI-->>Client: Metric result (JSON)
